# .shellcheckrc - ShellCheck configuration file for Rotkeeper
# This project uses standard, robust bash patterns that ShellCheck sometimes flags.
# We configure ShellCheck globally to ignore the following rules:

# Disable SC1090: ShellCheck can't follow non-constant source.
# Disable SC1091: Not following: file was not specified as input.
# Disable SC2034: Unused variables (commonly VERSION, VERBOSE, etc. for dispatchers/bumps).
# Disable SC2317: Command appears to be unreachable (unreachable code false positives for traps/guards).
# Disable SC2181: Check exit code directly (indirect check with $? is used intentionally).
# Disable SC2076: Remove quotes from =~ (used intentionally for literal substring checking).
# Disable SC2053: Quote right-hand side of == (glob matching is used/wanted here).
# Disable SC2155: Declare and assign separately (standard local assignments).

disable=SC1090,SC1091,SC2034,SC2317,SC2181,SC2076,SC2053,SC2155
